  "text_preview": "\"skating\" American Sign Language (ASL) ASL University ► American Sign Language: \"skating\" ROLLER SKATE: To sign \"skate,\" form your hands into \"bent V\" handshapes. Then put them in front of you, palms facing up. Alternate moving them forward and back a couple times. Memory tip: Think of the movement of a skater's feet. ROLLER SKATE: That handshape looks like this: Animation: \"ROLLER SKATE\" To sign SKATE as in I-C-E \"SKATE\" form your hands into \"X\" handshapes. Then put them in front of you, palms facing up. Alternate moving them forward and back a couple times. Memory tip: Think of the movement of a skater's feet. Think of the upturned \"X\" as representing the curved blade on the skates. ICE-SKATE: Here's a close-up of that handshape: There is a sign for \"rollerblading.\" As time goes on, I'm "
}
